Consider using `<Image />` from `next/image` or a custom image loader to automatically optimize images. This may incur additional usage or cost from your provider. See: https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/no-img-element","JSXOpeningElement",["1085"],["1086","1087"],["1088"],["1089","1090"],["1091"],["1092","1093"],["1094"],"react-hooks/exhaustive-deps","React Hook useEffect has missing dependencies: 'currentTime', 'getActiveAudioClips', 'getActiveVideo', 'getCurrentVideoClip', 'preloadNextClip', 'startAudioClip', 'startPlaybackLoop', 'stopAllAudio', and 'stopPlaybackLoop'. Either include them or remove the dependency array.","ArrayExpression",["1095"],["1096"],["1097","1098"],["1099"],["1100","1101"],["1102"],"react-hooks/refs","Error: Cannot access refs during render\n\nReact refs are values that are not needed for rendering. Refs should only be accessed outside of render, such as in event handlers or effects. Accessing a ref value (the `current` property) during render can cause your component not to update as expected (https://react.dev/reference/react/useRef).\n\n/Users/matthieublanc/Projects/storycraft/app/features/shared/hooks/use-debounce.ts:18:22\n  16 |         () =>\n  17 |             // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/refs\n> 18 |             debounce((...args: Parameters<T>) => {\n     |                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 19 |                 return callbackRef.current(...args);\n     | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n> 20 |             }, delay),\n     | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Passing a ref to a function may read its value during render\n  21 |         [delay],\n  22 |     );\n  23 | }",["1103"],["1104","1105"],["1106"],["1107","1108"],["1109"],{"messageId":"1110","fix":"1111","desc":"1112"},{"messageId":"1113","fix":"1114","desc":"1115"},{"kind":"1116","justification":"1117"},{"messageId":"1110","fix":"1118","desc":"1112"},{"messageId":"1113","fix":"1119","desc":"1115"},{"kind":"1116","justification":"1117"},{"messag